Source: lorica-hardened-profile
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Lorica Linux <lorica@example.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2

Package: lorica-hardened-profile
Architecture: all
Depends: lorica-base, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Lorica Linux maximum hardening profile
 Opt-in hardening overrides for high-security environments. Installs
 sysctl and GRUB drop-in configs that override lorica-base defaults
 with maximum hardening: panic on kernel warnings, disable SMT,
 SLUB debug, lockdown=confidentiality, block all ICMP, no ptrace.
 .
 WARNING: This profile impacts performance and breaks some debugging
 workflows. Review docs/hardening-decisions.md before installing.
 .
 Install via: apt install lorica-hardened-profile
